NavigateToSearchZone() - Static method in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Navigation
When this method is called, the robot determines the closest corner of the search zone from its current position (Entrance of the island).
NavigateToStartingZone() - Static method in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Navigation
In this method, the robot navigates back to the starting Zone from its current position on the island ObstacleAvoidance() method in the Object class is called if an obstacle is to be detected
NavigateXY() - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Navigation
In this method, the robot navigates to a given gridpoint, this method is called from within the NavigationToEntranceOfIslandFromStartZone() method.
Navigation - Class in ca.mcgill.ecse211.project
This class is primarily responsible for the navigation of the robot to the island from its starting zone, it is also responsible for the navigation of the robot to its starting zone from the island.
Navigation() - Constructor for class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Navigation
 
NAVIGATION_SLEEP - Static variable in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Resources
Time for which the navigation thread sleeps for
NavigationToEntranceOfIslandFromStartZone() - Method in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Navigation
In this method, assuming that the robot has completed ultrasonic localization and is at the appropriate gridpoint -(1,1) if the starting corner was 0 - the robot navigates to the entrance of the tunnel and stops.
NINETY_DEGREES - Static variable in class ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Resources
90 degrees
